<div id="review_2917635" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2917635" />
    <a title="Crystal" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/182835-crystal"><img alt="Crystal" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1608764683p2/182835.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2917635?book_show_action=true">Jul 10, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Crystal" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Crystal" href="/user/show/182835-crystal">Crystal</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">fans of romance, hope, and/or LM Montgomery</span></div>

        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/182835-crystal?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/182835-crystal?shelf=classics">classics</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2917635" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7471726036449693418">This is my favorite novel by LM Montgomery, even though it&apos;s not necessarily typical of her books. It is the sweetest romance I have ever read, full of laugh out loud moments and obnoxious &quot;villains&quot;. In fact, this book&apos;s annoying characters are on a par with Jane Austen&apos;s best. it&apos;s a great story of learning to be free of society&apos;s bonds and expectations, of finding love when and where least expected, and of the joys that come when you open your heart to them. I completely recommend this book. </span>
  <span id="freeText7471726036449693418" style="display:none">This is my favorite novel by LM Montgomery, even though it's not necessarily typical of her books. It is the sweetest romance I have ever read, full of laugh out loud moments and obnoxious "villains". In fact, this book's annoying characters are on a par with Jane Austen's best. it's a great story of learning to be free of society's bonds and expectations, of finding love when and where least expected, and of the joys that come when you open your heart to them. I completely recommend this book. It may be my favorite ever novel--definitely in the top 10. </span>
  <a data-text-id="7471726036449693418" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
