<div id="review_3359605400" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3359605400" />
    <a title="Antoinette" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5328952-antoinette"><img alt="Antoinette" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1503842818p2/5328952.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3359605400?book_show_action=true">Dec 30, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Antoinette" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Antoinette" href="/user/show/5328952-antoinette">Antoinette</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5328952-antoinette?shelf=canadian-literature">canadian-literature</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3359605400" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6179095533863364688">These are the words I would use to describe this book: quaint, charming, delightful, humorous and totally wonderful. I absolutely loved this book.<br/><br/>This book was written in the 1920’s. Many would call it old fashioned, but I loved going back to a time when being unmarried was considered scandalous. No, I don’t want to revisit those times. I prefer today, but it was so delicious to go back.<br/><br/>Valancy is 29 years old, unmarried and of course living with her mother. She had to keep busy all the time, or</span>
  <span id="freeText6179095533863364688" style="display:none">These are the words I would use to describe this book: quaint, charming, delightful, humorous and totally wonderful. I absolutely loved this book.<br /><br />This book was written in the 1920’s. Many would call it old fashioned, but I loved going back to a time when being unmarried was considered scandalous. No, I don’t want to revisit those times. I prefer today, but it was so delicious to go back.<br /><br />Valancy is 29 years old, unmarried and of course living with her mother. She had to keep busy all the time, or else she would get reprimanded. She was not allowed to speak up. Reading was considered slothful. All her relations made derisive comments about her marital status. Then one day, Valancy gets some news that makes her look at life differently.<br /><br />I loved cheering Valancy on. A late bloomer that finally blooms.<br /><br />A book I highly recommend!<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="6179095533863364688" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


